## [FAIL] Low — `dataUrls` prop for cover-slide `ImageGrid` not specified

**What is missing:** The A4b code snippet shows:
```ts
<ImageGrid
  cols={gridSpec.columns}
  images={gridSpec.cells}
  dataUrls={...}                  // ← placeholder, no expression given
  maxHeight={GRID_MAX_HEIGHT_COVER}
/>
```

The `{...}` placeholder leaves the `dataUrls` expression unspecified. `dataUrls` is a parallel array to the `images` prop. In the existing non-cover grid branch, the pattern is `gridImageDataUrls ?? slide.gridImages.map(() => null)`. For the cover branch with `images={gridSpec.cells}`, the correct expression is the same (`gridImageDataUrls ?? slide.gridImages.map(() => null)`), because `gridSpec.cells` is always a prefix of `slide.gridImages` (cells are sliced from index 0) so index alignment is preserved.

A developer who doesn't recognize this might write `gridSpec.cells.map(() => null)`, discarding the actual image data and rendering all cells as grey placeholders.

**Fix required:** Replace `dataUrls={...}` with `dataUrls={gridImageDataUrls ?? slide.gridImages.map(() => null)}` in the A4b code snippet.

